#: class-my-apps.php:758
msgid ""
"Abilities for searching the My Apps App Store, reading What can I do? "
"guides, and customizing the My Apps launcher."
msgstr ""
"Funktionen zum Durchsuchen des My Apps App Stores, Lesen der „Was kann ich "
"tun?“-Anleitungen und Anpassen des My Apps-Starters."

#: class-my-apps.php:774
msgid "Get All My Apps State"
msgstr "Gesamten My Apps-Status abrufen"

#: class-my-apps.php:775
msgid ""
"Returns the full My Apps launcher state, including background, visible app "
"order, and app metadata."
msgstr ""
"Gibt den vollständigen Status des My Apps-Starters zurück, einschließlich "
"Hintergrund, Reihenfolge der sichtbaren Apps und App-Metadaten."

#: class-my-apps.php:782
msgid ""
"Use this before answering questions about the user's My Apps launcher, "
"launcher apps, visible app order, hidden apps, app icons, app links, or "
"background. The result is the full current launcher state; use "
"visible_ordered for display order and each app's hidden field for visibility."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:795
msgid "Get What Can I Do Guides"
msgstr "„Was kann ich tun?“-Anleitungen abrufen"

#: class-my-apps.php:796
msgid ""
"Returns the default My Apps What can I do? guide catalog for answering what "
"users can do with WordPress."
msgstr ""
"Gibt den Standardkatalog der My Apps-„Was kann ich tun?“-Anleitungen zurück, "
"um zu beantworten, was Benutzer mit WordPress tun können."

#: class-my-apps.php:803
msgid "Optional guide slug to return one guide."
msgstr "Optionaler Anleitungs-Slug, um eine einzelne Anleitung zurückzugeben."

#: class-my-apps.php:807
msgid ""
"Optional search query matched against guide titles, descriptions, and steps."
msgstr ""
"Optionale Suchanfrage, die mit Titeln, Beschreibungen und Schritten der "
"Anleitungen abgeglichen wird."

#: class-my-apps.php:811
msgid "Optional maximum number of matching guides to return."
msgstr ""
"Optionale maximale Anzahl passender Anleitungen, die zurückgegeben werden "
"sollen."

#: class-my-apps.php:822
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks what they can do with WordPress, asks for "
"activity ideas, or asks for What can I do? guide steps. This returns only "
"the default recipes.json catalog; it does not include browser-local custom "
"blueprints or alternate App Store catalog sources."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:835
msgid "Search My Apps App Store"
msgstr "My Apps App Store durchsuchen"

#: class-my-apps.php:836
msgid ""
"Searches or browses the built-in My Apps App Store catalog of installable "
"apps and curated plugin recommendations."
msgstr ""
"Durchsucht oder öffnet den integrierten My Apps App Store-Katalog mit "
"installierbaren Apps und kuratierten Plugin-Empfehlungen."

#: class-my-apps.php:843
msgid ""
"Optional search query matched against app titles, descriptions, authors, "
"categories, paths, plugin slugs, and GitHub repositories."
msgstr ""
"Optionale Suchanfrage, die mit App-Titeln, Beschreibungen, Autoren, "
"Kategorien, Pfaden, Plugin-Slugs und GitHub-Repositories abgeglichen wird."

#: class-my-apps.php:847
msgid ""
"Optional App Store category to return, such as Apps, AI, Media, "
"Productivity, Social, Utility, Custom, or Other Plugins."
msgstr ""
"Optionale App Store-Kategorie, die zurückgegeben werden soll, zum Beispiel "
"Apps, KI, Medien, Produktivität, Social, Dienstprogramme, Eigene oder "
"Weitere Plugins."

#: class-my-apps.php:852
msgid ""
"Optional entry type filter. Use app for blueprint apps, plugin for curated "
"plugin recommendations, or all."
msgstr ""
"Optionaler Filter für den Eintragstyp. Verwende app für Blueprint-Apps, "
"plugin für kuratierte Plugin-Empfehlungen oder all."

#: class-my-apps.php:856
msgid ""
"Whether to include curated plugin recommendations. Defaults to the current "
"My Apps simplified WordPress mode setting."
msgstr ""
"Ob kuratierte Plugin-Empfehlungen eingeschlossen werden. Standard ist die "
"aktuelle My Apps-Einstellung für den vereinfachten WordPress-Modus."

#: class-my-apps.php:860
msgid "Optional maximum number of matching App Store entries to return."
msgstr ""
"Optionale maximale Anzahl passender App Store-Einträge, die zurückgegeben "
"werden sollen."

#: class-my-apps.php:871
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks whether My Apps has an app store, asks to search "
"or browse the app store, asks what apps can be installed from My Apps, or "
"asks about curated app/plugin recommendations. This reads the default "
"published catalog and cannot include browser-local custom blueprints or "
"alternate catalog source overrides."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:884
msgid "Set My Apps Background"
msgstr "My Apps-Hintergrund festlegen"

#: class-my-apps.php:885
msgid "Updates the My Apps launcher background preference."
msgstr "Aktualisiert die Hintergrundeinstellung des My Apps-Starters."

#: class-my-apps.php:893
msgid ""
"A preset background slug, image attachment ID, remote image URL, or safe CSS "
"color/gradient background."
msgstr ""
"Ein vordefinierter Hintergrund-Slug, eine Bild-Anhang-ID, eine entfernte "
"Bild-URL oder ein sicherer CSS-Farb- oder Verlaufs-Hintergrund."

#: class-my-apps.php:903
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks to change the My Apps launcher background. Pass "
"one accepted background slug, an image attachment ID, a remote image URL, or "
"a safe CSS color/gradient background."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:916
msgid "Add My Apps Icon"
msgstr "My Apps-Symbol hinzufügen"

#: class-my-apps.php:917
msgid "Adds a custom app icon to the My Apps launcher."
msgstr "Fügt dem My Apps-Starter ein eigenes App-Symbol hinzu."

#: class-my-apps.php:926
msgid "The app icon label shown in the launcher."
msgstr "Die im Starter angezeigte Beschriftung des App-Symbols."

#: class-my-apps.php:930 class-my-apps.php:972
msgid "The URL opened by the app icon."
msgstr "Die URL, die vom App-Symbol geöffnet wird."

#: class-my-apps.php:933
msgid "Optional icon. Omit all icon fields to use a generated letter icon."
msgstr ""
"Optionales Symbol. Lasse alle Symbolfelder leer, um ein generiertes "
"Buchstabensymbol zu verwenden."

#: class-my-apps.php:942
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks to add or pin an app icon to the My Apps "
"launcher. Provide a name and URL. Provide at most one icon value: icon_url, "
"dashicon, emoji, gradient, icon { type, value }, or use_favicon."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:955
msgid "Set My Apps App Details"
msgstr "My Apps-App-Details festlegen"

#: class-my-apps.php:956
msgid "Renames an app or changes its link in the My Apps launcher."
msgstr "Benennt eine App um oder ändert ihren Link im My Apps-Starter."

#: class-my-apps.php:964 class-my-apps.php:1009 class-my-apps.php:1047
msgid "The launcher app slug from my-apps/get-all."
msgstr "Der Starter-App-Slug aus my-apps/get-all."

#: class-my-apps.php:968
msgid "The app label shown in the launcher."
msgstr "Die im Starter angezeigte App-Beschriftung."

#: class-my-apps.php:976
msgid "When true, remove the custom name and URL override."
msgstr "Wenn wahr, werden eigener Name und eigene URL-Überschreibung entfernt."

#: class-my-apps.php:986
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks to rename an app, change an app shortcut link, "
"or revert a custom app name/link. First call my-apps/get-all to find the "
"slug. Provide name and/or url, or set revert to true."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:999
msgid "Set My Apps App Icon"
msgstr "My Apps-App-Symbol festlegen"

#: class-my-apps.php:1000
msgid "Updates the icon graphic for an existing My Apps launcher app."
msgstr "Aktualisiert die Symbolgrafik einer vorhandenen My Apps-Starter-App."

#: class-my-apps.php:1013
msgid ""
"When true, remove the custom icon override and return to the app-provided "
"icon."
msgstr ""
"Wenn wahr, wird die eigene Symbolüberschreibung entfernt und zum von der App "
"bereitgestellten Symbol zurückgekehrt."

#: class-my-apps.php:1016
msgid "New icon value. Use icon type letter to force a generated letter icon."
msgstr ""
"Neuer Symbolwert. Verwende den Symboltyp letter, um ein generiertes "
"Buchstabensymbol zu erzwingen."

#: class-my-apps.php:1025
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks to change the icon for an existing My Apps "
"launcher app. First call my-apps/get-all to find the slug. Provide exactly "
"one icon value unless reverting."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1038
msgid "Set My Apps App Visibility"
msgstr "My Apps-App-Sichtbarkeit festlegen"

#: class-my-apps.php:1039
msgid "Shows or hides an app in the My Apps launcher."
msgstr "Zeigt oder verbirgt eine App im My Apps-Starter."

#: class-my-apps.php:1051
msgid "Whether the app should be hidden from the launcher."
msgstr "Ob die App im Starter verborgen werden soll."

#: class-my-apps.php:1061
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks to hide, show, restore, or unhide one app in the "
"My Apps launcher. First call my-apps/get-all to find the slug. Set hidden to "
"true to hide the app, or false to restore it. For multiple visibility or "
"order changes, prefer my-apps/set-visible-ordered."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1074
msgid "Set My Apps Visible Ordered Apps"
msgstr "Sichtbare My Apps-Apps in Reihenfolge festlegen"

#: class-my-apps.php:1075
msgid "Sets the visible My Apps launcher icons and their order."
msgstr "Legt die sichtbaren My Apps-Starter-Symbole und ihre Reihenfolge fest."

#: class-my-apps.php:1083
msgid ""
"Launcher app slugs that should be visible, in display order. Apps not listed "
"are hidden."
msgstr ""
"Starter-App-Slugs, die sichtbar sein sollen, in Anzeigereihenfolge. Nicht "
"aufgeführte Apps werden verborgen."

#: class-my-apps.php:1096
msgid ""
"Use this when the user asks to reorder visible apps, hide multiple apps, or "
"show only specific apps. First call my-apps/get-all to find app slugs and "
"the current visible_ordered array. Pass visible_ordered as the complete "
"desired visible slug list in display order; every app omitted from "
"visible_ordered is hidden. Verify the response using visible_ordered and "
"each app's hidden field."
msgstr ""

#: class-my-apps.php:1122
msgid "The icon representation type."
msgstr "Der Darstellungstyp des Symbols."

#: class-my-apps.php:1126
msgid "The icon value for icon_url, dashicon, emoji, or gradient."
msgstr "Der Symbolwert für icon_url, Dashicon, Emoji oder Verlauf."

#: class-my-apps.php:1133
msgid "An image URL to use as the app icon."
msgstr "Eine Bild-URL, die als App-Symbol verwendet wird."

#: class-my-apps.php:1137
msgid "A WordPress Dashicon class, such as dashicons-admin-site."
msgstr "Eine WordPress-Dashicon-Klasse, zum Beispiel dashicons-admin-site."

#: class-my-apps.php:1141
msgid "An emoji to use as the app icon."
msgstr "Ein Emoji, das als App-Symbol verwendet wird."

#: class-my-apps.php:1145
msgid "A safe CSS color or gradient used behind the default app glyph."
msgstr ""
"Eine sichere CSS-Farbe oder ein Verlauf hinter dem Standard-App-Zeichen."

#: class-my-apps.php:1149
msgid "Use the app URL origin favicon when no other icon value is supplied."
msgstr ""
"Verwendet das Favicon der App-URL, wenn kein anderer Symbolwert angegeben "
"ist."

